      "id": "alphabet",
      "icon": "🔤",
      "title": "Alphabet",
      "subtitle": "L-alfabett Malti: 30 letters",
      "intro": "The Maltese alphabet has 30 letters, including a few you won't find in English (ċ, ġ, ħ, ż, għ). Tap each to hear its sound.",
      "facts": [
        "There are 30 letters in all: 24 consonants and 6 vowels (a, e, i, o, u and ie).",
        "That last vowel, ie, is written with two symbols but counts as a single letter.",
        "Five letters belong to Maltese alone: ċ, ġ, ħ, ż and għ (and għ counts as one).",
        "Spelling is friendly here: Maltese is largely written as it's spoken, so once you know the sounds you can read almost anything.",
        "Underneath it's a Semitic language (Arabic roots), layered over the centuries with Italian and English."
      ],
