      "id": "syllables",
      "icon": "🔡",
      "title": "Syllables",
      "subtitle": "Is-Sillabi: hearing the beats in a word",
      "intro": "Break a word into beats and Maltese spelling falls into place. Every sound steps forward where you can hear and write it.",
      "facts": [
        "One vowel = one beat.",
        "Every beat after the first opens on a consonant sound.",
        "When two consonants collide mid-word, the break falls between them: kel-ma, fes-ta.",
        "Hear it: omm → omm; mara → ma-ra; kelma → kel-ma."
      ],
